# Frontend Environment Variables

## Required Variables

### Backend API
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000
# Production: https://your-backend.railway.app

### Authentication
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=your_secret_key_here
# Must match backend BETTER_AUTH_SECRET exactly
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32

BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://your-app.vercel.app

### Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/database
# Example: postgresql://user:pass@ep-example.us-east-2.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require
# Note: Frontend uses standard postgresql:// (not postgresql+asyncpg://)

## Optional Variables

### Next.js Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=TODO App
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_VERSION=1.0.0

### Analytics (if using Vercel Analytics)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ANALYTICS_ID=your_analytics_id

## Notes

- Never commit .env files to git
- Use .env.local for local development
- Use Vercel dashboard for production environment variables
- BETTER_AUTH_SECRET must match backend exactly
- BACKEND_URL must point to your deployed backend API
- BETTER_AUTH_URL must match your frontend deployment URL
- DATABASE_URL format differs from backend (no +asyncpg)
